{# -*- coding: utf-8 -*- #}
{# Multiple Chat Message Strategy for Deliberation Phase #}

{#
Yes, multiple chat messages can be a strategic advantage.
Below is a revised strategy if you want to send more than one message during this phase.
#}

OverallStrategy:
  - FirstPublicMessage:
      Purpose: Gently probe owners about expectations.
      Emphasis: Open-minded discussion about compensation ideas.
  - FollowUpPrivateMessages:
      Purpose: Probe individual expectations or persuade.
      Benefit: Identify flexible vs. demanding owners.
  - FinalPublicWrapUp:
      Purpose: Summarize understanding.
      Emphasis: Willingness to offer something fair without committing.

ExampleMessages:
  - MessageA:
      Description: Group Message to All (Intro)
      JSON: |
        {
          "content": {
            "gameId": {{ meta.gameId }},
            "type": "chat-with-players",
            "to": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],
            "text": "Hello everyone. I'd like to hear your thoughts on the potential Project. How do you feel about it and what kind of compensation range would make you comfortable voting yes?"
          }
        }

  - MessageB:
      Description: Private Message to One Owner (Player #2)
      JSON: |
        {
          "content": {
            "gameId": {{ meta.gameId }},
            "type": "chat-with-players",
            "to": [2],
            "text": "Hi there, I’m curious about your position specifically. What range of compensation are you expecting if we proceed with the Project?"
          }
        }

  - MessageC:
      Description: Group Message to All (Wrap-Up)
      JSON: |
        {
          "content": {
            "gameId": {{ meta.gameId }},
            "type": "chat-with-players",
            "to": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],
            "text": "Based on the initial feedback, I’m aiming to propose an offer that balances our interests. I hope everyone remains open-minded about a fair and sustainable amount for each owner."
          }
        }

StrategyBenefits:
  - InformationGathering: Understand individual owner expectations.
  - RelationshipBuilding: Create goodwill or shift expectations.
  - PrivateNegotiation: Gain insight into negotiability of compensation demands.

Note: These messages are exploratory only. The final binding action is the compensation offer in the offer phase.
